  "prompt": "I had one set of pictures of my wife and another set for me. I merged the two. How do I unmerge and start over?",
  "response": "To unmerge your sets of pictures, you can follow these steps depending on how you merged them:\n\n1. **Manual Sorting**: If you merged the pictures into a single folder or album, you can manually separate them. Go through the merged folder and move your wife's pictures back to her original folder and your pictures to yours. You may want to use tags or sort by date to help identify which pictures belong to whom.\n\n2. **Use Software**: If you used photo editing software (like Photoshop), you can check for layers. If each set is on a different layer, you can simply hide or delete the layer that corresponds to the photos you want to separate.\n\n3. **File Management**: If you added pictures to a specific application (like a photo management app), check if the app supports undoing actions or if there is a way to restore a previous state.\n\n4. **Backup**: If you have a backup (like cloud storage or external hard drive), you can restore your original sets of pictures from there.\n\n5. **Organize by Date or Tags**: If organizing manually is too cumbersome, try sorting by date taken or using a tagging system to efficiently label and separate the pictures.\n\nIf you provide more details about how you merged the pictures, I can offer more tailored advice!",
